[Chikungunya outbreaks continue to pop up around various Philippines islands this year (2013), with new ones reported above. One can expect these outbreaks to continue as long as the vector mosquito populations are abundant. Unless vector control measures are quickly implemented, these outbreaks are likely to continue. There is no commercially available vaccine to prevent chikungunya virus infections, so the only effective measure to prevent transmission of the virus is through timely control of mosquito vectors.

A map of the Philippines can be accessed at http://www.mapsofworld.com/philippines/maps/Philippines-Location.jpg, Negros Occidental province at http://healthmap.org/r/7H_W, and Camarines Norte province at http://healthmap.org/r/7H_X. - Mod.TY]
